ci\u003eThe Ugly American\u003c/i\u003e (1958), \u003ci\u003eFail-Safe\u003c/i\u003e (1962) and \u003ci\u003eThe 480\u003c/i\u003e (1965).\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eHe was born in Sheldon, Iowa. His family moved to Los Angeles, California, when he was age 4. Burdick attended Stanford University and Oxford University where he earned a Ph.D. degree in psychology, and he worked at the department of Political Science at the University of California. In 1956, his critically acclaimed novel \u003ci\u003eThe Ninth Wave\u003c/i\u003e, a Houghton Mifflin Literary Fellowship winner, was published. At the end of the 1950s, he was among the first members of the Society for General Systems Research. He died suddenly of a heart attack at the age of 46.","isGrAuthor":false,"works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":18},"profileImageUrl":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/authors/1417211190i/49284._UX200_CR0,48,200,200_.jpg","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/49284.Eugene_Burdick","user":null,"viewerIsFollowing":null,"followers":{"__typename":"ContributorFollowersConnection","totalCount":16}},"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.XSBAtEiR63nUVy0fIKsD7A":{"id":"kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.XSBAtEiR63nUVy0fIKsD7A","__typename":"Contributor","name":"Harvey Wheeler","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/203131.Harvey_Wheeler","isGrAuthor":false},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.qLrJVgxj2cJsSwsjt_Siww":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.qLrJVgxj2cJsSwsjt_Siww","__typename":"Book","legacyId":354259,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/354259.Fail_Safe","title":"Fail-Safe","titleComplete":"Fail-Safe","description":"Something has gone wrong. A group of American bombers armed with nuclear weapons is streaking past the fail-safe point, beyond recall, and no one knows why. Their destination—Moscow.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eIn a bomb shelter beneath the White House, the calm young president